===Etymology===
Sanskrit, ''to [[stop]]''

===Noun===
'''virama''' ([[viramas]])

# A [[diacritic]] used in most writing systems of the Indian subcontinent to signify the lack of an inherent vowel.
# A sign which serves the same purpose in any writing system.

